{
  "response": "<span style="color: #3b82f6">Both fixes are done with zero lint errors.

**Issue 1 — Picker visibility on Android APK:** Added `color="#000000"` and `dropdownIconColor="#000000"` to every `<Picker>` component, and `color="#000000"` to every `<Picker.Item>` in `location.tsx`, `profile.tsx`, and `profile.ios.tsx`. This forces the selected value text to render in black regardless of the Android theme in release builds.

**Issue 2 — Password visibility toggle:** Added eye icon toggles (using `Ionicons` `eye-outline`/`eye-off-outline`) to all password fields across 4 files — login screen (1 field), register modal (2 fields: password + confirm), and both profile password-change modals (3 fields each: current, new, confirm).</span>"
}

{
  "response": "<span style="color: #3b82f6">The root cause was a **string mismatch**: onboarding saved emoji-prefixed strings like `'🎵 Música'` to the database, but the profile edit screen's `AVAILABLE_INTERESTS` used plain strings like `'Música'`. So `editInterests.includes(interest)` never matched — nothing appeared selected, and deselection was impossible.

Both fixes applied to `profile.tsx` and `profile.ios.tsx`:

1. **`AVAILABLE_INTERESTS` and `AVAILABLE_PERSONALITY`** now use the exact same emoji-prefixed strings as `app/onboarding/interests.tsx`, so database values match the chip labels.
2. **`toggleInterest` / `togglePersonality`** now use the functional `setState(prev => ...)` form to avoid stale closure bugs, with `console.log` on each toggle.</span>"
}

